.SH "NAME"
rifle \- rangerz file opener
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBrifle\fR [\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-f\fR \fI\s-1FLAGS\s0\fR] [\fB\-l\fR] [\fB\-p\fR \fI\s-1KEYWORD\s0\fR]
[\fB\-w\fR \fI\s-1PROGRAM\s0\fR] \fIfiles\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
rifle be a bangin file executor dat allows fo' complex file type checking,
written ta hook up tha needz of tha file manager \fIranger\fR.  riflez strength lies
in automatically determinin file types, dependin on which programs are
installed on tha system, even without any user interaction.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-f\fR \fI\s-1FLAGS\s0\fR" 14
.IX Item "-f FLAGS"
Specify flags fo' openin tha files.  Flags is lettas dat chizzlez how tha fuck the
program is executed. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! This type'a shiznit happens all tha time.  Any combination of flags will work.  Freestylin uppercase
flags will negate tha effect of all previously used lowercase flagz of tha same
letter.
.Sp
Table of all flags:
 f   fork program ta background
 r   run program as root, rockin sudo
 t   run program up in a separate terminal, as specified by \f(CW$TERMCMD\fR
.IP "\fB\-l\fR" 14
.IX Item "-l"
List all possible ways ta open tha specified files.  Each line will contain shiznit up in tha format of \fIid:label:flags:command\fR. \fIid\fR is tha identification number n' shit. \fIlabel\fR be a arbitrary strang dat was specified fo' dis command, \fIflags\fR is tha flags dat is used by default, n' \fIcommand\fR is tha command dat is goin ta be executed.
.IP "\fB\-p\fR \fI\s-1KEYWORD\s0\fR" 14
.IX Item "-p KEYWORD"
Pick a method ta open tha files.
.Sp
\&\fI\s-1KEYWORD\s0\fR is either tha \s-1ID\s0 number listed by \f(CW\*(C`rifle \-l\*(C'\fR or a strang dat matches a label up in tha configuration file.
.IP "\fB\-w\fR \fI\s-1PROGRAM\s0\fR" 14
.IX Item "-w PROGRAM"
Open tha filez wit tha program \fI\s-1PROGRAM\s0\fR
.IP "\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR" 14
.IX Item "-h, --help"
Print a list of options n' exit.
.SH "FILES"
.IX Header "FILES"
rifle shares configuration filez wit ranger, though ranger aint required in
order ta use rifle.  Da configuration file \fIrifle.conf\fR is sposed ta fuckin be at
\&\fI~/.config/ranger/rifle.conf\fR.
.PP
This file specifies patterns fo' determinin tha commandz ta open filez with.
Da syntax is busted lyrics bout up in tha commentz of tha default \fIrifle.conf\fR dat ships
with ranger n' shit.  To obtain it, you need ta run: \f(CW\*(C`ranger \-\-copy\-config=rifle\*(C'\fR
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.IX Header "ENVIRONMENT"
.IP "\s-1EDITOR\s0" 8
.IX Item "EDITOR"
Determines which editor ta use fo' editin filez (in tha default \fIrifle.conf\fR).
.IP "\s-1PAGER\s0" 8
.IX Item "PAGER"
Determines which pager ta use fo' displayin filez (in tha default \fIrifle.conf\fR).
.IP "\s-1TERMCMD\s0" 8
.IX Item "TERMCMD"
Determines tha terminal emulator command fo' use wit tha \fIt\fR flag.  It be required dat tha value is tha path ta a executable file which accepts tha \*(L"\-e \s-1COMMAND\s0\*(R" argument.
.IP "\s-1XDG_CONFIG_HOME\s0" 8
.IX Item "XDG_CONFIG_HOME"
Specifies tha directory fo' configuration files. Defaults ta \fI\f(CI$HOME\fI/.config\fR.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.IX Header "EXAMPLES"
List all tha different methods:
.PP
.Vb 4
\& $ rifle \-l helloworld.py
\& 0:editor::"$EDITOR" \-\- "$@"
\& 1:pager::"$PAGER" \-\- "$@"
\& 2:::python \-\- "$1"
.Ve
.PP
Display its content by openin it wit \*(L"cat\*(R":
.PP
.Vb 2
\& $ rifle \-w pussaaaaay helloworld.py
\& print("Wuz crackalackin' World!")
.Ve
.PP
Run it by pickin tha method 2, which calls 'python \*(-- \*(L"$1\*(R"':
.PP
.Vb 2
\& $ rifle \-p 2 helloworld.py
\& Wuz crackalackin' World!
.Ve
.PP
Display tha file up in a pager inside a freshly smoked up terminal, run as root:
.PP
.Vb 1
\& $ rifle \-p 1 \-f tr helloworld.py
.Ve
